        <div type="letter">
            <div type="text">
                <opener>
                    <placeName><hi rend="print">15, Lombard Street. E.C.</hi></placeName>
                    <date>20 Feb. 1868</date>
                    <salute>My dear M<hi rend="superscript">r</hi>. Darwin</salute>
                </opener>
                <div type="transcription">
                     
<p>I feel much flattered by your kind letter &amp; will certainly let you know as soon as I can make up my great mind about Pangenesis.<ref target="#foot.f1"/></p>
<p>I want to hear what can be said against it.</p>
<p>The whole book has, I need not say, been full of interest for me. The article in the Athenæum will do no harm   it overshoots the mark so absurdly.<ref target="#foot.f2"/></p>
<p>If you get other cases of mixed races reverting to Barbarism, please let me know.<ref target="#foot.f3"/> It would be an additional argument for me.</p>
<p>I have been away from home a good deal this week, &amp; have not yet been able to find Desmarest, but hope to send you both the books this evening.<ref target="#foot.f4"/></p>
<p>Believe me, dear M<hi rend="superscript">r</hi>. Darwin | Yours most sincerely | John Lubbock</p>
<p>P.S. I send you the Zeits. Desmarest I cannot find for the moment.</p>
<p>JL</p> 
                </div>
            </div>

            
            
            
        </div>

        

        

